 Symptoms:
- Container shows “Exited” status
- docker ps doesn't show the container
- Service inaccessible via browser
- Container keeps restarting

Diagnosis:
docker logs [container_name]
docker ps -a | grep [container_name]
docker inspect [container_name]
df -h

Common Causes:
- Configuration syntax error (YAML indentation)
- Port already in use by another service
- Required dependency not running (database down)
- Out of disk space
- Volume mount path doesn't exist
- Corrupted container state

Solutions:

For config errors:
docker logs [container_name] –tail 50
nano /opt/docker/docker-compose.yml
# Fix syntax, save
docker compose up -d [container_name]

For port conflicts:
ss -tlnp | grep [port]
# Stop conflicting service or change port in docker-compose.yml

For missing dependencies:
docker ps | grep [dependency]
docker compose up -d [dependency]
docker compose up -d [container_name]

For disk space:
df -h
docker system prune -a
# Or delete old files/backups

For corrupted state:
docker compose down [container_name]
docker compose up -d [container_name]

Prevention:
- Validate YAML before applying (use yamllint.com)
- Check logs immediately after starting new services
- Monitor disk space regularly
- Use depends_on in docker-compose.yml
